args:
The prince succeeds in securing Siren's
cooperation while his allies distract Barbary.
When the dragon sings her song, it charms
Barbary long enough for the party to trap her
once more in the space between worlds.
Yar, ye bilge rats better scurry outta yer\nholes before I raze this island to cinders!
Hail, Barbary, you vile fiend!\nCome for us if you have the sand!
At last, the deck-swabbin' cowards show\ntheir mugs. Ready yerselves for death,\nme hearties! Gahaaaar har har!
Do not let your spirit falter! Her attacks\nare random and haphazardâ€”we are\nnot yet in any true danger.
Celliera is right. Let us hide ourselves in\nthe jungle and call out to distract her.
Okay, I'll give it a shot!
That treasure belongs to Erasmus\nand Simon, Barbary! Give it back!
Gar, it be the stone-headed lass again!
I got just the thing for a prissy\nloudmouth such as ye, girlie!
You've got this, Estelle! Keep talking!
Ha! If there's one thing I'm good at,\nit's PREACHING!
Hey, Barbary! Why don't you bring\nsome of those tentacles this way?!
I've had a hankering for octopus lately,\nand I think you're just the ticket!
Gar, ye foulsome lass! How dare ye\ntalk down to a pirate such as me?!
I'm gonna kill ye special, so I am!
Perhaps we don't need to enrage her\nQUITE so much, Celliera?
Wrong! This is all part of my plan.\nGo, {player_name}! Go now!
No need to worry!\nI have this well in hand.
Then I leave it to you. Farewell!
If things get too hairy, I want all of you\nto fall back. You understand?
No one here wishes to be a martyr...
And yet, running from that brute\nis the last thing I want to do!
Does your guilt over the lost treasure\ncontinue to drive you so?
Noâ€”this is about my pride as a preacher!
I won't be satisfied unless I can reform\nthis dastardly pirate into a fine,\nupstanding member of society!
Ha ha ha! Oh, but I had almost forgotten\nthe passion of you mortals!
Simon was fond of saying, ï¼‚I won't be\nsatisfied until I find the treasure.ï¼‚
Your passions have returned me to those\nheady days of yore, and given me a new\nstrength to take on Barbary!
Come at us, pirate! We shall take all\nyou can give out and return it tenfold!
Meanwhile, the prince and his group head\nto a cave on the other side of the island...
It would be easy to get lost forever\nin a twisty cave like this.
It's like a natural maze... As if the land\nitself were pushing people away.
I pray we are able to find Siren soon.
Our friends are counting on us.
Wait, that voice... It must be Siren!
Still, we'll need to be careful not to\nfall victim to that song's charms.
We'll need to...be careful... So careful...
Augh, I almost stopped right there!\nCome on, we have to keep going.
...Okay, that should do it. Let's go!
Siren! Siren, please listen to me!
Oh wow. You're, like, human.\nWhat are you DOING here?
I thought all your people totally\nhated me and stuff...
Aw, she doesn't seem so bad.
I think the rumors about her\nmight have been a little off.

Ohmigosh, are people STILL telling all
those nasty stories about me? They're
TOTALLY not true! I'm a good dragon!
Seriously, I am...
We aren't here to judge you, Sirenâ€”\nwe're here to ask for your help.
Oh wow. That totally explains all the\nnoise and whatever coming from the\nother side of the island.
Even now, our comrades are desperately\ntrying to withstand Barbary's assault.
We need you to sing for us so Barbary\nlowers her defenses. Will you help?
You're not, like, making this up, right?\nIt's not some prank or whatever?\nYou actually NEED me?
We need you AND your song.
Is it really so strange a request that\nyou feel the need to doubt us so?
No, it's just... I mean, nobody's wanted\nme to sing in, like, FOREVS.
Ah, right. Erasmus told us he'd warned\nyou about that a few times before.
Oh, and he also wants you to know\nthat he doesn't hate you.
Really. He's just doing his job as the\nguardian dragon of sailors.
In truth, he said your song was beautiful.
And I know we can use that song\nto charm even Barbary!
But okay! I'll totally sing for you guys!
Thank you, Siren! Now please,\nwe have to hurry!
Curse you, Barbary! You truly are\nthe most treacherous of fiends!
There must be a yawning emptiness where\nyour heart would be for you to cut down\nthe entire forest in pursuit of us!
Gar, THERE ye be! No more runnin'\nme trig lads and lassesâ€”I'm gonna\nbe finishin' ye for good!
Is this the end for us?\n{player_name}...please hurry!
So if you're here, that means Siren...
She's right behind me. Sorry for the delay!
Reinforcements, eh?! Ain't no matter!\nThe locker's got room for all'a ye!
It's time for me to siiiiing!
Gahar har har! Yer grand scheme is to fell\nme with some blasted heartfelt shanty?!\nWhat sort'a cockamamie plot is...is...
Yar, but that be a lovely voice...
Then it's time for the otherworld fragment!
What'n the hell? Noooo!\nCurse yer booooones!
Come on, everyoneâ€”it's time for us\nto finish Barbary off for good.
